binds fields to dynamic values 
does onChange for you 

HTML
<input type="text" v-model="username" />

JS
const app = new Vue({ 
  el: '#app',
  data: { username: 'Michael' } 
});

when this example site is loaded, 
the <input> will already be pre-filled with 'Michael', 
the starting value of username. Then, whenever the <input> 
is modified by the user, the username data value will 
automatically change to the value typed in by the user.

***********
.number = convert value to a number 
.trim   = removes whitespace from the begining and endings of form values 
.lazy   = only update on change 

more: https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-model